<HEADLINE> Barak to Visit Washington on July 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Israel's new Prime Minister
Ehud Barak will visit the United States from July 15 to 19,
diplomatic sources said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Barak spoke briefly to U.S. President Bill Clinton by
telephone on Monday night, telling him he intended to meet first
with Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat, Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak and King Abdullah of Jordan before visiting Washington.
</P>
<P>
In Washington, Barak and Clinton will review the next steps
toward peace between Israel and the Palestinians and discuss how
to revive talks with Syria.
</P>
<P>
The United States wants Israel to complete implementation of
last October's Wye agreement with the Palestinians, including
another withdrawal from part of the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Clinton has said he would outline his views right after
talking to Bakar.
</P>
<P>
Barak will also meet Secretary of State Madeleine Albright
and Secretary of Defense William Cohen during his stay in
Washington. 
</P>
</TEXT>
