<HEADLINE> Sweden Beats Mexico in Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA, Spain, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Sweden rallied from a 1-2
deficit to defeat Mexico in a five-set men's volleybal battle on
Wednesday in the 20th World University Games.
</P>
<P>
After falling behind by 22-25, 25-19 and 20-25 in the first
three sets, Sweden stepped up and won the last sets 25-19, 15-12.
</P>
<P>
In anathor men's action, volleyball power Russia met no trouble
as they dismissed Estonia 25-19, 25-23 and 25-15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
