<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Blast South Africa at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA, Spain, July 7 (Xinhua) -- China thrashed South Africa
122-30 in a women's basketball group game in the 20th World
University Games on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
South Africa proved to be no match to China in speed and
technical combination and was outscored 68-21 in the first half.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, they lost any nerves and got a meagre 9
points to China's 54.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Taipei edged Brazil 81-80, while another Asian team
Japan lost 64-76 to Canada.
</P>
<P>
Men's action saw the Chinese men's team succumbed to Finland 46-
75, South Korea met their Waterloo and lost 98-88 to Greece and
Japan was held off by the Netherlands 97-76. 
</P>
</TEXT>
