<DOCNO> XIE19990708.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Unveils New tariff Structure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Tariff Commission of Zimbabwe
Wednesday unveiled a new tariff structure which seeks to enhance
competitiveness and export growth of the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
The new tariff structure proposed that rates of duty on
international goods, parts and tools which are pegged at 15 to 30
percent, five to 15 percent and 15 percent respectively be pegged
at between 10 to 25 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the new structure the commission also proposed that duty for
 protected goods including all sensitive products which are pegged
at 60 to 100 percent be revised to 40 to 70 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the commission proposed retaining duty on other
capital and merit goods, raw materials and primary goods, finished
goods which are currently pegged at zero to five percent, five
percent and 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
Addressing representatives from various sectors at a one-day
tariff review consultative workshop in Harare, Zimbabwean Tariff
Commissioner Owen Tshabangu said the proposed tariff structure is
expected to open up room for small- and medium-scale businesses
which have been disadvantaged by the current structure.
</P>
<P>
"This new structure is the bench-mark for further tariff reform
which will ultimately lead to low or relatively uniform structure
in the future," said the commissioner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990708.0018 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 17:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lebanese Kurds Protest Against Death Sentence for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of Kurds in Lebanon
Wednesday held a demonstration here, demanding the Turkish
government to reverse the death sentence passed on the Kurdish
rebel leader Abdullah Ocalan.
</P>
<P>
The number of the demonstrators was put at 7,000, including
Kurdish children, women and elderly. They marched one kilometer
from Cora area in southern Beirut to the nearby United Nations
building.
</P>
<P>
Some protesters shouted anti-Turkish government slogans,
carrying pro-Ocalan banners and his portraits.
</P>
<P>
They submitted a statement to U.N. representatives, asking the
intervention of the U.N. for the release of Ocalan.
</P>
<P>
Last month, a Turkish court handed down the death sentence on
Ocalan, the leader of the Kurdish Workers Party (PKK) on charges
of treason and separatism.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish government held Ocalan responsible for the deaths
of 37,000 people in the Kurds' 15-year-old guerrilla war for
autonomy in southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of Kurds are living in Lebanon, of which
25,000 have been granted Lebanese citizenship since the 1950s.
</P>
</TEXT>
