<HEADLINE> Over 17000 NATO Troops Pass Through Thessaloniki for Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 17,500 NATO soldiers have
passed through the northern Greek port of Thessaloniki on their
way to Macedonia and Kosovo from February 10 and July 4.
</P>
<P>
The Thessaloniki-based Macedonian Press Agency (MPA) quoted the
Greek Defense Ministry as saying on Wednesday that 298 aircraft,
91 ships and 9 trains arrived in Thessaloniki at that period of
time carrying a total of 17,538 soldiers, 10,546 vehicles of all
types, 3,131 towed vehicles, 3,607 containers, 214 armored tanks
and 1,710 armored personnel carriers.
</P>
<P>
410 Russian solders will arrive at the port of Thessaloniki on
July 14 on board 5 ships in order to participate in the
peacekeeping force in Kosovo. 
