<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Denies Mistreatment of Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian government
Wednesday denied that refugees in its country have been dealt with
unfairly, defending that refugees have been treated in compliance
with the law.
</P>
<P>
Permanent Secretary of the Ministry of Home Affairs Bernard S.
Mchomvu was commenting on the latest report by the Human Rights
Watch organization which said that Tanzania has violated human
rights by confining refugees to camps unfairly.
</P>
<P>
The report alleged that the Tanzanian army conducted a
house-to-house check in refugee camps largely in late 1997 and
early 1998 on the grounds that this was necessary to protect
Tanzanian citizens living near the border with Burundi.
</P>
<P>
In the report, Executive Director of the Africa Division of
Human Rights Watch Peter Takirambudde said that Tanzania has a
long and generous tradition of hospitality to refugees, but there
exists cases that refugees are dragged from their homes and
treated like criminals solely because they are refugees.
</P>
<P>
Mchomvu said that Tanzania has a generous tradition of
hospitality especially in the handling of refugees.
</P>
<P>
He said that the country last year amended the National
Refugees Act of 1966, and the new law has a special provision that
refugees must be taken care of in a particular area instead of
being mixed with the citizens.
</P>
<P>
The permanent secretary observed that the government will not
tolerate any misconduct or criminal actions by refugees.
</P>
<P>
He said when some refugees complained last year that they were
stripped of their belongings and separated from their families,
the Tanzanian and Rwandan governments requested the concerned
refugees to forward their complaints but they have not done so.
</P>
<P>
More than 300,000 refugees from Burundi, Rwanda, Congo (K) and
other African countries are accommodated in Tanzania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990708.0027 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 18:24 </DATE_TIME>
