<HEADLINE> Drugs Found on Liberia Ship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus police Wednesday found five
kilograms and 260 grams of cocaine on a ship of "Pittsburg," under
Liberian flag.
</P>
<P>
Police said that on July 2, the German captain of the ship
discovered the drugs hidden in the ship's hold, the Cyprus News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
He immediately notified the shipowner company and received
instructions to deliver the drugs to the Cyprus authorities.
</P>
<P>
In the early morning Wednesday, the "Pittsburg" reached Cyprus'
southern Limassol port and the captain handed over the cocaine to
Cypriot policemen.
</P>
<P>
The ship originally sailed from Equator to Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued by Cyprus police, the
street value of the cocaine found aboard the ship was 400,000
Cyprus pounds (800,000 U.S. dollars). 
</P>
