<P>
 Adjei-Mensah expressed satisfaction at efforts made to
implement the project, saying, "we have come a long way, and
treaded a very difficult path to reach this stage of the Keta Sea
Defense Project today."
</P>
<P>
 He commended the Presidency for its profound interest and
commitment that has seen to the take-off of the project.
</P>
<P>
 Robinson noted that the project is a major one, the largest
civil works by the bank in West Africa in recent years.
</P>
<P>
 Richard Lowry, Chief Operations Officer and Executive
Vice-President of Great Lakes and Dredge, said they are excited by
the project and are looking forward to it. 
</P>
