<HEADLINE> Ministers Finalize Draft Cease-fire Pact on Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The ministers of foreign affairs and
defense finalized the draft cease-fire agreement on the conflict
in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) on Wednesday evening
here in Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
Zambian Presidential Affairs Minister Eric Silwamba said at a
press conference that the regional ministers met in Lusaka from
June 29 to July 7, 1999 to finalize the draft cease-fire agreement
on the conflict in the DRC and the Modalities and Time-table for
the implementation of the cease-fire.
</P>
<P>
Silwamba said the ministers and representatives from the 14
Southern African Development Community (SADC) and the
international community reached agreement on the above mentioned
documents and adopted them unanimously.
</P>
<P>
The ministers and representatives will report to the regional
heads of state who will decide on the date for the signature of
the cease-fire agreement, he added.
</P>
<P>
Silwamba described the meeting as "extremely successful" and
expressed his confidence that the long-expected summit will be
held here soon at which the documents will be signed by all the
warring parties involved in the 11-month war.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the rebel Congolese Rally for Democracy
(RCD) and the Movement for the Liberation of Congo (MLC) also
attended the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
