<HEADLINE> Dow Moves to New Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
moved to new record high Wednesday as investors were awaiting
corporate earning reports in the second quarter.
</P>
<P>
The blue chip index closed up 52.24 at 11,187.36, surpassing
the record closing high of 11,139.24 set last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index rose 7.74 at 1,395.86 and the
technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 6.26 at 2,743.04,
both moving into new record territories.
</P>
<P>
The stocks rallied as Wall Street analysts expected most U.S.
companies to report robust earnings for the second quarter. First
Call Corp. said in a survey that analysts expect the earnings of
the 500 companies in the Standard &AMP; Poor's stock average to rise
11.4 percent for that quarter.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 1.70 at 656.47 and the American
Stock Exchange index fell 2.75 at 802.14. The Russell 2000 index
of smaller companies fell 3.86 to 452.69.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a a 4-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,696 down, 1,306 up and 559
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 776.83 million shares from 718.48
million in the previous session. 
</P>
