<HEADLINE> Women's World Cup Final A Sellout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The final between host team the
United States and China is a sellout at Rose Bowl on July 10,
according to women's World Cup organizers.
</P>
<P>
Marla Messing, President and chief executive official of the
Organizing Committee, announced that the July 10 doubleheader, which
also features the Third place playoff between Norway and Brazil, is
sold out and a crowd of more than 85,000 is expected -- a record for
a women's-only sporting event.
</P>
