<HEADLINE> American Players Respect Their Chinese Opponents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The third women's World Cup
final will be played between China and host team the United States
at Rose Bowl on Saturday and the American players and team officials
showed deep respect for the Chinese team.
</P>
<P>
Forward Tiffeny Milbrett, who had scored three goals in the
tournament, said:"The Chinese team have technical speed that is
unbelievable. Their vision of the field is amazing."
</P>
<P>
Kate Sobrero said:"Every single player on that team is strong, fast
and technical."
</P>
<P>
"They send numbers forward and they love to attack," said
American assistant coach Lauren Gregg, the team's resident
tactician, "They find the most dangerous, penetrative options as
quickly as possible."
</P>
<P>
The American head coach Tony DiCicco said:"They don't make a lot
of mistakes."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team play to win, unlike several other teams in the
tournament that sit back on defense and pray for a tie when taking
on the Americans. China have been winners of two out of three
encounters against the American team.
</P>
<P>
The American players, especially the forwards, know that their
Chinese rivals won't take any cheap shots.
</P>
<P>
"There's going to be some exciting, excellent soccer for
everyone to enjoy," said Milbrett, "It's going to be a challenge for
us and it'll be exciting to try and create against one of the
world's best defenses."
</P>
<P>
Gregg said she believes China's striker Sun Wen, not Mia Hamm,is
the best finisher in the world right now and the final will be a
game for the ages.
</P>
<P>
"The final on Saturday will be one of the finest soccer matches
ever played," said Gregg. 
</P>
