<HEADLINE> Vietnam Communist Party Leader Visits Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- General Secretary of the Vietnam
Communist Party Le Kha Phieu arrived here Wednesday for an eight-
day official visit to Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Le Kha Phieu will meet Cuban President Fidel Castro on Thursday.
He will be conferred "Jose Marti Order", the highest for
foreigners.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnam Communist Party leader was accompanied by Vice
Premier and Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Can, Chief of the Party's
Foreign Relations Commission Nguyen Van Son and other high ranking
officials.
</P>
<P>
Castro was the first head of state to visit Vietnam after the U.
S. invasion to the country.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban leader visited Vietnam again in November, 1995 in his
Asian tour also including China and Japan. 
</P>
