<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchanges on
Wednesday closed slightly up with the benchmark IPC index rising
by 12.52 points, or 0.21 percent, at 5,931.24 points.
</P>
<P>
Operators exchanged 72.949 million shares for an amount of some
114.606 million U.S. dollars against 107.793 million shares worth
177.823 million dollars on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood at 9.50 to one dollar for
sale and 9.20 for purchase in the main exchange houses of the
Mexico City, compared with 9.50 for sale and 9.15 for purchase on
Tuesday. 
