<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS -- President Tejan Kabbah Wednesday called on his fellow
Sierra Leoneans to learn to "forgive and forget" in rehabilitating
the war-torn west African country, a report reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking before signing the peace accord with the rebels in
Togolese capital Lome, the president introduced a mutilated woman
and a child to the audience, saying that they are the victims of
the war waged by the rebel Revolutionary United Front's forces. (
Nigeria-SLeone Peace)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian State Duma and the NATO Parliamentary
Assembly plan to resume cooperation shortly, the Interfax news
agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was announced by Duma chairman Gennady Seleznyov
and Javier Ruperes, head of the NATO Parliamentary Assembly,
following their talks in St. Petersburg, Interfax said. (Russia-
NATO-Parliaments)
</P>
<P>
