<HEADLINE> New Entry Record at Palma Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA, Spain, July 7 (Xinhua) -- As the 20th World University
Games entered the sixth day, a new record of the number of
participants was officially registered at 5,776, the International
University Sports Federation (FISU) said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The previous record was 5,740, at the 1995 Universiade in
Fukuoka, Japan.
</P>
<P>
The fresh new record is stronly predicted to be further
bettered at this Universiade, FISU said in a statement today.
</P>
<P>
"These figures show the success of the FISU promotion of the
Universiade to the sports student association of the world," FISU
secretary general Roch Campana said.
</P>
<P>
"Of course, the fact that the Universiade is organized in Spain
means that the European countries could send larger teams," said
Campana. "But last Universiade in 1997 was also organized in
Europe, in Sicily."
</P>
<P>
"As far as the Palma Universiade is concerned, FISU is also
glad that this participation success does not cause an
accommodation problem for the athletes," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
