<HEADLINE> Peru's Exports to the U.S. Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Peruvian exports to the United
States have risen 11.56 percent to 1.97 billion U.S. dollars in
1998 from 1.77 billion dollars in 1997, local media reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the U.S. Embassy in Peru as saying that the
Peruvian exports to the United States include copper, gold,
petroleum, coffee, textiles, sugar, wood and asparagus.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Peru's imports from the United States have
risen 2.04 percent, from 1.96 billion dollars to 2 billion dollars,
according to U.S. diplomats.
</P>
<P>
The diplomats said that U.S. companies are interested in
investing more in Peru.
