<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Comeback Fu Looks Rusty in Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA, Spain, July 7 (Xinhua) -- China's three-time Olympic
diving champion Fu Mingxia still struggled to shake off the rust
after her comeback despite winning the women's 10-meter platform
title Wednesday in the 20th World University Games.
</P>
<P>
The student of the prestigious Beijing-based Qinghua University
nearly botched her last dive, a back 1 1/2 somersault with 3 1/2
twist, which only earned her 57.600 points.
</P>
<P>
But Fu, who will celebrate her 22nd birthday next month, still
took the gold with a total of 522.390 points.
</P>
<P>
Her teammate Wang Rui, who was awarded the highest score of 80.
640 in her last dive, settled for the silver in 522.000, with the
bronze going to Canadian Anne Montminy, who garnered 504.930
points.
</P>
<P>
"My performance was just so-so," said Fu, who became sports
fans' idol after her Olympic victories in the 1992 and 1996 Games.
She retired at the age of 19 after Atlanta, a sad news for her
fans.
</P>
<P>
"Since this is the first time for me to attend the world
university games, I am happy to win," she said.
</P>
<P>
From her triumph at the 1991 world swimming championships in
Perth, when the 12-year-old became the youngest diving world
champion, Fu has grown into a confident 21-year-old with a ready
laugh and twinkling coffee-brown eyes. She also dyed her black
hair brown.
</P>
<P>
Fu's next major target is to make another splash in next year's
Olympics, by bracing herself against any obstacles ahead.
</P>
<P>
"Now there are lots of excellent divers in China, so I must
first go through the national qualification events, " she added.
</P>
<P>
Fu's coach Yu Fen was satisfied with her protege's performance.
"This is the first time for her to compete in platform since her
comeback and some of her dives were even better than in Atlanta
Olympics," she said.
</P>
<P>
"We have one year's time prior to the Sydney Olympics, and she
can further build up her confidence through more competitions," Yu
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
