<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uruguay Adopts New Measures Against Arms Proliferation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay's Interior Minister
Guillermo Sterling on Wednesday announced new measures fighting
against the proliferation of firearms in the country.
</P>
<P>
The new measures were worked out by the Commission for the
Study of the Proliferation of Firearms, said Sterling.
</P>
<P>
According to Congressman Javier Garcia, the proliferation of
firearms in the Uruguayan society is an "alarming phenomenon", as
there are more than 700,000 pieces in the country, which could be
translated to one piece for every four people.
</P>
<P>
At present there are 572,000 registered firearms and
approximately 172,000 unregistered, of which only 10 percent are
in the hands of security or defense personnel, said the legislator.
</P>
<P>
Gun-shot is the fourth main reason of death for children under
the age of fourteen in Uruguay, following traffic accidents,
drowning and burns.
</P>
<P>
There were 188 adolescents died of gun-shots in the past 10
years, of which 49 were below the age of 14 and 139 were aged
between 15 and 19. 
</P>
</TEXT>
