In Group C, Chinese Taipei managed a one-point victory over
Brazil 81-80, sailing into the elimination as runners-up after
Lithuania outscored the Czech Republic 64-47 with a clean slate.
</P>
<P>
In Group D, Russia was the only squad that remained unbeaten
after they dominated their match against Portugal 73-45, however
Portugal still qualified for the quarterfinals on two wins against
one loss.
</P>
<P>
Spain, Ukraine, Lithuania and Russia were the four teams that
kept their slate intact, while Canada, the United States, Chinese
Taipei and Portugal qualified as runners-up in their respective
groups.
</P>
<P>
The eliminated teams like Japan, Sweden, China, South Africa,
the Czech Republic, Brazil, Mexico and South Korea will vie for
the ninth to 16th places. 
</P>
</TEXT>
