<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Tea Export Increases in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam exported 12,000 tons of tea
in the first six months of this year, an increase of 1.4 percent
compared with the same period of last year, Vietnam News Agency
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam plans to export 35,000 tons of tea this year, mainly to
its traditional markets in Japan and the Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has put additional 2,000 hectares of land under tea
cultivation this year, and another 2,000 hectares will be planted
with tea from now to the end of the year, bringing the country's
total tea acreage to 74,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
Most of the tea areas are in Vietnam's northern mountainous
region and several central highland provinces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
