<DOCNO> XIE19990708.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mayon's Temper Unpredictable, Philippine Experts say </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The activity at Mayon Volcano has
reached a plateau and volcanologists have voiced uncertainty about
what will happen next.
</P>
<P>
A report from the Philippine Institute of Volcanology and
Seismology (Phivolcs) said Thursday that Alert Level 2 is still in
effect.
</P>
<P>
Monitoring equipment detected four high frequency volcanic
earthquakes, ground deformation surveys showed sustained inflation
in the southeast slope of the volcano, and moderate steam emission
was observed rising from the crater during the 24-hour observation
period. the Phivolcs said.
</P>
<P>
July Sabit, a member of a monitoring team from the Phivolcs
told reporters Wednesday that the next few days would see whether
it would erupt or simmer down as in 1993.
</P>
<P>
"It is really hard to tell what will happen next," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Sabit, in 1993 volcanologists issued alert level 2
for Mayon but activity at the volcano died down after reaching a
plateau.
</P>
<P>
"It will depend on the activities in a volcano's magma
chamber," he explained. "There would be times when it would be
active and then it would die down naturally but when it is able to
sustain its activities, then that is when an eruption takes
place." 
</P>
</TEXT>
