<HEADLINE> 5 Killed in German Cargo Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 8 (Xinhua) -- All the five persons, one
American national and four Indian nationals, were killed when a
cargo plane of the German Lufthansa Airlines crashed Wednesday
evening in the Kathmandu Valley, the Tribhuvan International
Airport (TIA) said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An airport source said their bodies were found scattered. Among
the dead, Captain Ricardo Nicolas Gonhalez was an American
citizen.
</P>
<P>
The New Delhi-bound Boeing 727 cargo plane crashed near a hill
nine minutes after it took off from the TIA Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
It was carrying 21 tons of carpet and was flown by the
Lufthansa Cargo India Pvt. Ltd, a joint venture of Lufthansa and
the London-based Hinduja Cargo Services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
