<HEADLINE> Paes Breezes to Second Round in Hall of Fame Men's Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Days after winning the doubles
and mixed doubles titles at Wimbledon, India's Leander Paes showed
his singles game at the Hall of Fame men's tennis championships in
Rhode Island, United States, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The defending champion breezed into the second round with a 6-1,
6-3 victory over Yugoslavia's Nenad Zimonjic.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old Paes, not known as a big server, hit seven aces
and didn't face a break point. He played well-placed angle shots
and volleys to repeatedly torment his opponent,
</P>
<P>
Paes will meet top-seeded Wayne Ferreira of South Africa on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In other actions Wednesday, American Chris Woodruff beat third-
seeded David Prinosil of Germany 6-2, 6-4 in a second-round match,
and fourth-seeded Andrew Ilie of Australia rallied to oust Italy's
Christiano Carrati 5-7, 6-4, 7-5 in the first-round. 
