<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The long-awaited line-up list of
the Chart Pattana Party (CPP) for the government reshuffle has
been submitted to Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai, a
well-informed source said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The source, who refused to be named, said that CPP has
requested for Minister of Prime Minister's Office and Deputy
Minister of Transportation and Communication.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the core ruling party, the Democrat Party, will get
the deputy premiership and the science portfolio.
</P>
<P>
As coalition partners had all finished their reshuffle list,
Prime Minister Chuan is expected to propose the list of new
cabinet members to King Bhumibol Adulyadej later Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper reports said that PM's Office Minister Pitak
Intrawityanunt and Labor Minister Sompong Amornviwat, both from
CPP, will become the biggest casualties in the cabinet shake-up by
losing their posts.
</P>
<P>
Suchon Champunot, a CPP "dark-horse," is expected to replace
Pitak, while senior party member Prachuab Chaiyasarn will be
shifted from the post of university affairs minister to labor
minister. 
</P>
