<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Privatize National Airlines Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government will
privatize the national airlines, Biman, by June next year by
off-loading 49 percent of its shares through a strategic
partnership, press reports here said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Privatization would help the national carrier offset its
losses, Civil Aviation Minister Mosharraf Hossain was quoted as
saying at the parliament on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"I am hopeful that we would be able to off-load 49 percent of
the share of Biman by June next year," he said.
</P>
<P>
Various irregularities had long been dogging the national flag
carrier, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hossain added that a total of 34.2 million taka (about 705,000
U.S. dollars) remained outstanding with 25 travel agencies as
ticket money of the national airlines.
</P>
<P>
Corruption and irregularities, such as unauthorized payment of
incentive commissions, unplanned expenditure for sales promotion
and transport of Bangladeshi deported from abroad, have caused
losses to Biman, the reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
