the cyberage, was launched Thursday by Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad.
</P>
<P>
The launching was witnessed by some of the world's top
information technology industry leaders who are here to attend the
Multimedia Super Corridor (MSC) Third International Advisory Panel
(IAP) meeting.
</P>
<P>
Cyberjaya, situated about 40 km south of Kuala Lumpur, is the
main component of the MSC, a 750 sq. km zone designated as a hub
for the development of multimedia products and services.
</P>
<P>
The Cyberjaya township is built on a 2,800-hectare site based
on an environment friendly concept.
</P>
<P>
One of its main components, the Universiti Multimedia Telekom
(UMMT) is scheduled for official opening Friday by Mahathir.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the launching, Mahathir chaired the IAP meeting,
which is being attended by 25 IAP members or their
representatives.
</P>
<P>
The IAP, comprising multimedia industry leaders and gurus, was
formed to advise the government on the MSC.
</P>
<P>
The inaugural meeting was held in Stanford University,
California, USA, two years ago while the second was organized here
last year.
</P>
<P>
The three-day meeting is expected to re-evaluate the progress
of the MSC project.
</P>
<P>
Among those present are Dr. Stan Shih, chairman and CEO of Acer
Incorporated; Serge Tchuruk, chairman and CEO of Alcatel Alsthom;
and Bob Bishop, chairman of Silicon Graphic World Trade
Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Two new faces in the IAP at the meeting are Dr. Terry Cutler,
director of Cutler and Company from Australia; and Professor Wang
Xuan of Peking University. 
