<HEADLINE> Cyberjaya to Contribute to Economic Recovery: Mahathir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CYBERJAYA, Malaysia, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad said Thursday the timely completion of Cyberjaya will
contribute significantly to Malaysia's ongoing economic recovery.
</P>
<P>
"The timely completion of the first phase of Cyberjaya's
development, despite our recent economic difficulties, is proof of
our commitment to all investors in the MSC (Multimedia Super
Corridor)," he said at the launching of Cyberjaya, one of the
world's intelligent cities and the nerve center of the MSC.
</P>
<P>
He said that even during the recent downturn the MSC was given
priority in terms of both budget allocation and policy support.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated the government's full commitment towards ensuring
the continued progress of the development of Cyberjaya on a fast
track basis.
</P>
<P>
Cyberjaya is located next to Putrajaya, the new federal
administrative center, about 40 km south of Kuala Lumpur.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said Malaysia must continue to innovate and be even
more responsive to investors to attract knowledge from around the
world to help create the vibrant, creative, networked society in
Cyberjaya.
</P>
<P>
"Given its potential and importance, Malaysia has designated
MSC as its next engine of growth," he said.
</P>
<P>
Malaysians, by and large, knew that the MSC represented their
future and thus support and participation in this venture had
permeated the whole society, said Mahathir.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said Malaysia did not view initiatives
similar to the MSC in other parts of the world as competitors but
more as opportunities for networking and collaboration.
</P>
<P>
The MSC is a 750 sq. km area south of Kuala Lumpur designated
as a hub for the development of multimedia services and products.
</P>
<P>
"We have started to build bridges with these initiatives and
together hope to overcome the myriad of cross-border issues coming
in the wake of the Information Age," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said there were already 32 world-class web-shapers
which had obtained MSC status.
</P>
<P>
He said from 285 companies which had applied for the status,
225 had obtained it and 21 companies, including eight MSC-status
firms, were already located in Cyberjaya.
</P>
<P>
"All MSC-status companies are expected to move into one of the
four designated cybercities within a year of Cyberjaya's
opening...I would also like to call on other MSC-status companies
to relocate to Cyberjaya early to reap the full benefits," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said the official launching of Cyberjaya also signified the
last major building block of the MSC was in place and the
completion of several key complementary "soft" infrastructure such
as the various cyberlaws enacted.
</P>
<P>
"We have also put into place the necessary support in terms of
training and human resource programs for the development of
technopreneurs and knowledge workers," he said.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's commitment towards developing the MSC and multimedia
industry for the long term was vindicated by the latest statistics
from around the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said in the United States, although the high
technology services sector accounted for only 5.5 percent of
American gross domestic product in 1997, it produced almost 40
percent of GDP growth over the preceding two years.
</P>
<P>
Cyberjaya is one of the MSC's two flagship intelligent cities
-- the other one being Putrajaya, the neighboring new federal
government administration capital.
</P>
<P>
"Cyberjaya is a greenfield development uniquely designed to be
a global test-bed," he said. "We are not held back by rigid or
entrenched practices and policies. Cyberjaya will be a unique
blend of the best from East and West evolving to take on its own
creative culture." 
</P>
</TEXT>
