<HEADLINE> Papua New Guinea's Prime Minister Tenders Resignation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Papua New Guinea's Prime Minister
Bill Skate on Thursday tendered his resignation to Governor-
General Sir Silas Atopare, but reserved his right to re-nomination
of himself for the post.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Port Moresby, Skate told reporters
that he would leave it to the government and members of parliament
to decide if he should be re-nominated when the national
parliament resumes on July 13.
</P>
<P>
"It is only they who will decide to tell me completely to phase
out and not to be re-nominated."
</P>
<P>
His resignation came as the coalition partner, the People's
Democratic Movement (PDM), joined the country's opposition last
month.
</P>
<P>
The breakaway of PDM, which has about 40 seats in the 109-seat
parliament, means Skate could not survive the no-confidence motion
vote against him scheduled for July 13. 
</P>
</TEXT>
