<HEADLINE> Chinese Exporters Urged to Increase Competitiveness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official has urged
Chinese exporters, especially those in developed coastal areas, to
increase their competitiveness through restructuring industries
and the economy as a whole.
</P>
<P>
State Councilor Wu Yi made the call during her recent trip to
Shandong, a coastal province in east China.
</P>
<P>
She spoke highly of foreign-funded companies that have
mushroomed in China over the past two decades, calling them an
important force in the country's export sector.
</P>
<P>
She urged local governments to sum up past experiences and
further improve the investment environment.
</P>
<P>
Wu was in Shandong, from July 5-8, to attend a national meeting
on exploring the rural market. During her stay, the state
councilor also visited local villages and village-based companies
involved in the processing and marketing of farm products.
