<HEADLINE> China to Build Tourism Zone With Italian Features </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- China and Italy will jointly invest
90 million U.S. dollars to build a scenic zone with Italian
features in the northern Tianjin Municipality.
</P>
<P>
A letter of intent to this effect was signed here yesterday
evening by local government officials from Tianjin and the
Lombardy Region, Italy.
</P>
<P>
According to the document, a group of old, Italian-style
buildings that have existed in downtown Tianjin for a long time
will be built into a tourism and trading compound -- the Tianjin
Italian Scenic Zone.
</P>
<P>
A number of modern Italian streets, gardens, squares and
sculptures will be replicated in the zone. There will also be
shops selling Italian goods, restaurants providing Italian food,
and hotels making the guests feel as though they are in Italy.
</P>
<P>
The developers of the project include the Tianjin Liantong
Construction Development Co., Ltd., the Agenzia per la Cina of
Italy, and the Finlombarda S.P.A..
</P>
<P>
Tianjin, a major port city in China, is called by some as a "
world exposition on architecture" for its large number of foreign-
style buildings.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
