<HEADLINE> Shanghai Installs Street Condom Vendors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- As part of a citywide promotion of
safe and healthy sex, 200 automatic condom vendors have been
installed in the streets of this largest metropolis in China today.
</P>
<P>
The machines, installed in public places such as supermarkets,
hotels and universities, attracted many interested passers-by. The
authorities say the automatic vendors target local residents as
well as tourists and other transients.
</P>
<P>
There are already over 1,000 condom retailers around the city.
In 1998, 11.12 percent of men in Shanghai used condoms, which is
said to be quite a high percentage compared with other Chinese
cities.
</P>
<P>
In related developments today, a large-scale exhibition
entitled "Sex and Healthy Reproduction" and the Shanghai Modern
Family Planning Consultation Center were opened in the city.
</P>
</TEXT>
