<HEADLINE> Australia Opens Up for Chinese Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Australia is to become the first "
western" country to open its tourist market for Chinese people and
from the end of this month more Chinese will have their dream of
sightseeing there fulfilled, as the limit on the number of
tourists is to be lifted.
</P>
<P>
An agreement was reached over this matter by the governments of
the two countries in Shanghai last April.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Haicheng, a business planning manager with the Beijing
China Tourist Agency, said here today that newly-wed couples
joining the company's "Meeting in the Garden of Eden" wedding tour
program will become the first group of Chinese tourists holding
travel passports to go to Australia.
</P>
<P>
An increasingly large number of Chinese people with a monthly
income of over 2,000 yuan say they are willing to travel outside
the country, according to surveys made by China National Tourism
Administration in recent years.
</P>
<P>
However, their wish is often obstructed by complicated
formalities required for applying for formal passports, because
only a few southeast Asian countries acknowledge Chinese travel
passports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
