<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Euro Pegged at New Record Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The euro fell to another new low on
Thursday, with a European Central Bank reference rate of 1.0182
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday the euro's rate was 1.0222 dollars, while the
previous record low of 1.0221 dollars had been set on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's euro rate corresponded to 1.9209 marks per dollar,
compared with 1.9133 marks on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The euro was steady against other major currencies, with the
ECB issuing reference rates of 0.6544 pounds (0.6563), 124.72 yen
(124.77), and 1.6029 Swiss francs (1.6034).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile German shares slipped into the loss zone in a session
in which brokers said investors were concerned about the euro. By
mid- afternoon, the DAX Index stood at 5,581.56 points, down 6.94
points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
