friendly feelings of the Japanese Government and people towards
China.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a reception celebrating the inauguration of "The '
99 China-Japan Year of Cultural Friendship" activity only one and
a half hours after his arrival, the Prime Minister expressed
sincere pleasure over the visit at a time when China is preparing
major celebrations for the 50th anniversary of its founding and
the 20th anniversary of the signing of the China-Japan Cultural
Exchange Agreement.
</P>
<P>
Since the normalization of relations between Japan and China
27 years ago dialogue and communication have greatly increased,"
he said, adding that while about to embrace the new century, the
two countries should further consolidate their mutual
understanding and trust, which were fostered over many years.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, cultural exchanges between the two countries are of
great significance," he added, expressing the hope the present
cultural year activity would help further deepen understanding and
promote ties.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Cultural Minister Sun Jiazheng noted at the reception
that the cultural year activity was agreed in the joint
declaration issued by the two countries during President Jiang
Zemin's visit to Japan late last year. He voiced the hope the
activity would help deepen understanding between the two peoples
and push forward relations between them.
</P>
<P>
According to the activity plan, more than 30 joint cultural
events including art performances, symposiums and exhibitions will
be held in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
