<HEADLINE> Famous Chinese Architect Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Bo, a prestigious Chinese
architect who designed the Great Hall of the People, died on July
1 at the age of 88.
</P>
<P>
He presided over and directed the designing of more than 100
key projects in his lifetime, including the Cultural Palace of the
Nationalities and Beijing Friendship Hotel.
</P>
<P>
Zhang was a deputy to the 4th National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
He was born in Guangzhou, capital city of south China's
Guangdong Province, on April 12, 1911. He graduated from the
former Central University based in Nanjing in 1934. Since then,
Zhang has devoted all his life to architectural designing work. He
had been working at Beijing Municipal Research Institute on
Architectural Design since 1951.
</P>
<P>
A funeral ceremony was held in Zhang Bo memory at Babaoshan
Revolutionary Cemetery yesterday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
