Ministers Council of the Organization of African Unity (OAU).
</P>
<P>
During the three-day session which will start on Friday,
African foreign ministers will prepare the agenda of OAU's 35th
summit, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The summit will be opened on Monday in the Algerian capital and
run for three days.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers will discuss the disputes and civil wars
in seven African countries, namely Somalia, the Comoros, Angola,
Sierra Leone, the Republic of Democratic Congo, Guinea Bissau and
Burundi, the news agency quoted OAU sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The ministers will get acquainted with a report submitted by OAU
secretary general on regional and international efforts to seek
peaceful solutions to the conflicts in the countries.
</P>
<P>
Intensive contacts are expected to be held during or on the
sidelines of the council session on the crisis in Democratic Congo
and the Great Lakes region, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The council will also examine the border conflicts between
Eritrea and Ethiopia, which have entered the second year, after
getting acquainted with the two countries' viewpoints.
</P>
<P>
The ministers will deal with the developments of the relations
between Libya and Britain and the United States.
</P>
<P>
The Middle East peace process and ways of promoting the
African-Arab cooperation will also be on the agenda, the news
agency added. 
</P>
