<HEADLINE> Import, Export Volume Up in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's ports of entry handled
32.9 billion US dollars of goods in the first half of this year,
up 20.5 percent over the same 1998 period, latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The import volume reached 14.2 billion US dollars, up 24.2
percent, and the export volume, 18.7 billion US dollars,
representing an increase of 17.8 percent, Shanghai Customs said
today.
</P>
<P>
The increase was prompted by the surge of general-trade imports
and the recovering economies following the ending of the Asian
financial crisis, analysts noted.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's imports and exports, China's largest trade port,
account for more than one fifth of the country's total. 
</P>
