<DOCNO> XIE19990708.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Railway Transport Up in First Half of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Railway transport maintained a
steady increase in the first half of 1999, according to statistics
from the Ministry of Railways.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry reports that trains in China carried cargo of 774
million tons and 481 million passengers during the period,
increasing by 2.6 percent and 6.7 percent over the same period of
last year, respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the railway departments earned 49.1 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also show that trains carried 2.43 million people
daily on average in June. Included in the total were 616,000 long-
distance journeys, up 9.3 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The amount of containers transported by rail stood at 303,500
TEUs or 2.67 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the transport of coal shipped in June
reached 27,700 freight cars daily on average. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
