<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Struggling in the effects of a five-
week layoff, third seed Marcelo Rios of Chile lost to Morocco's
Younes El Aynaoui in straight sets at the second round of the
Swiss Open on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
El Aynaoui, 33rd in the ATP rankings, toppled the world number
nine 7-6 (7-5), 7-6 (7-5), ending Rios' return to competition
after more than a month off.
</P>
<P>
The former world No.1, who played his first event since French
Open, showed rusty form and could never get started against the
North African challenger.
</P>
