dropping the first in a tiebreaker. In the 12th game of the second
set, Rios made three unforced errors to bring about a further
tiebreaker.
</P>
<P>
El Aynaoui moved into a wining position with a perfect serve
for two match points. Rios saved the first but couldn't reach a
forehand to the corner on the second.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean reached a semi-final here a year ago, but has had
up-and-down results at the 1,050-meter-high venue in six
appearances. 
