<HEADLINE> UCI: No Positive Case for Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The International Cycling Union(UCI)
flatly denied reports that a Tour de France cyclist tested
positive for corticosteroids after the race's prologue.
</P>
<P>
French sports daily L'Equipe claimed Thursday that one of four
riders tested were found to have taken corticosteroids after
Saturday's prologue.
</P>
<P>
"There was not one positive case," the UCI's spokesman Enrico
Carpani was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Corticosteroids, anti-inflammatory and painkilling drugs which
are not classed as steroids, are banned unless prescribed by
doctors for specific medical conditions such as asthma and
rhinitis.
</P>
<P>
Four cyclists were tested after Saturday's prologue, including
the winner of the stage Lance Armstrong of the United States.
</P>
<P>
Denmark's Bo Hamburger, Manuel Beltran of Spain and Colombian
Joaquim Castelblanco were the others tested. 
