<DOCNO> XIE19990708.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Conference Will Promote Sino-Foreign Cooperation in Environment Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A high ranking Chinese official has
called on the whole of society to appreciate the significance of
protecting the ozone layer and the promotion of international
cooperation in environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao made the remarks today at a meeting of
the organizing committee for the 11th annual conference of the
signatories of the Montreal Protocol on Substances Which Deplete
the Ozone Layer to be held in Beijing from November 29-December 3.
</P>
<P>
"The meeting will hopefully exert a positive influence on
international cooperation in protecting the ozone layer and
further fulfill international treaties," said Wen, who is the
chairman of the organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the Chinese government has always attached
much importance to the protection of the ozone layer, and holding
such a meeting in China proves that the country's efforts to
protect the ozone layer has gained international recognition.
</P>
<P>
The depletion of the ozone layer, first discovered in the 1970s,
became an issue of global concern in the 1980s when the
international community started to seek ways to avoid further
damage to the ozone layer which deflects harmful ultraviolet rays
from the sun.
</P>
<P>
The international community signed the Vienna Convention for
the Protection of the Ozone Layer in 1985, setting the rules for
international cooperation in the project. Two years later,
countries signed the Montreal Protocol, setting out the framework
for international cooperation in the field.
</P>
<P>
An annual meeting has been held by the signatories in their
respective countries, now totaling 168, since 1987, and more than
1,000 representatives are expected at this year's meeting in
Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
