<HEADLINE> German Telecom Companies Makes Huge Investments in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- German telecommunications companies
are expected to invest more than 6.8 billion dollars this year
amid the increasing competition in the telephone sector, German
news agency DPA reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Among the planned figures, almost 1.94 billion dollars are
being invested by Deutsche Telekom's competitors to set up
additional fixed-network capacity, said Klaus-Dieter Scheurle,
president of the Telecommunications and Post Regulatory Agency.
</P>
<P>
He said he expected the growth in the telephone industry would
have positive effects on employment, noting that for the first
time, payroll reductions at Deutsche Telekom would be completely
balanced out by new jobs offered by its competitors.
</P>
<P>
Scheurle said that the number of new jobs offered by the
competitors would grow by a projected one-third this year, or more
than 50,000 positions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
