<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 50 Injured in Bangladesh Nationwide Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- At least one man was killed and about
50 others were injured in Bangladesh on Thursday during a
dawn-to-dusk nationwide hartal (strike) organized by the
opposition alliance.
</P>
<P>
A passenger bus was attacked by pro-hartal activists during the
shutdown in the capital city and an old man, who was traveling in
the bus, was seriously injured. He died after being rushed to the
Dhaka Medical College Hospital, sources said.
</P>
<P>
Several bomb blasts were reported in the capital city, where at
least 50 persons were injured at different places during the
hartal hours, but no major clashes between pro- and anti-hartal
activists were reported either in the capital or in other parts of
the country.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 5,000 policemen and Bangladesh Rifles personnel were
deployed in the capital to maintain law and order during the
strike.
</P>
<P>
Reports said one policeman was killed and at least 10 people,
including seven policemen, were injured in bomb explosions
Wednesday night in central Dhaka, when pro-hartal activists held
torch processions to drum up support for the hartal.
</P>
<P>
This was the seventh nationwide shutdown this year called by
the four-party opposition alliance, comprising the major
opposition -- the Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP), the Jatiya
Party, the Jamaat-e-Islami and the Islami Oikya Jote.
</P>
<P>
The opposition staged the hartal across the country to protest
against the passage in the parliament of what they called an
"anti-people" budget, "conspiracy" for gas export, soaring prices
of essentials, deteriorating law and order situation and power and
water crisis.
</P>
<P>
The hartal was aimed at delivering people from their sufferings
and safeguarding the country's independence and sovereignty
through compelling the government to resign and hand over power to
a caretaker government, opposition leader and BNP Chairperson
Khaleda Zia said.
</P>
<P>
Under a fresh program announced by the alliance's Central
Liaison Committee, the four parties would organize separate
demonstrations across the country under their respective party
banners on July 16, and stage road marches from the capital city
of Dhaka to different parts of the country between July 25 and 27.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
