<HEADLINE> Sharif Briefs Army Chief, Ministers on Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif Thursday chaired a high-level meeting here soon after his
return from a visit to the United States and Britain to discuss
the situation arising from the Pakistan-U.S. joint statement on
Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
General Pervez Musharraf, chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff
Committee and army chief, attended the meeting along with cabinet
ministers and senior officials.
</P>
<P>
No official comment was available so far, but informed sources
said the prime minister briefed the meeting on his talks with U.S.
President Bill Clinton and British Prime Minister Tony Blair.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also reviewed the situation arising from the joint
statement issued after talks between Sharif and Clinton, which
evoked strong criticism from opposition parities and retired army
generals in Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Sharif air-dashed to Washington in the wee hours of Sunday and
held three hours of talks with Clinton on the Kashmir tension
between Pakistan and India.
</P>
<P>
In the joint statement issued after the meeting, Sharif agreed
to persuade the Mujahedeen (holy war fighters) to withdraw from
the peaks they are occupying in the India-held Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Sharif returned here Thursday afternoon from London where he
discussed the Kashmir situation with Blair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
