<HEADLINE> Four People Sentenced To Death In North Central China For Homicide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Four Chinese men were sentenced to
death in the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region recently for using
explosives, intentional homicide, and robbery after a ruling by
the Yinchuan Intermediate People's Court last week.
</P>
<P>
The court also sentenced 9 others people to prison terms of
from 4 to 10 years for robbery, aiding and abetting, providing
false documents, and covering up for the 4 defendants.
</P>
<P>
According to the court, Xie Jianwen, Yang Jie, Yang Jun, and
Zhang Yanbin broke into a dynamite warehouse at the Lingxin Coal
Mine and stole dynamite early on the morning of March 31 and blew
up a police car with it on April 20, killing 4 policemen.
</P>
<P>
Prior to this, the 4 men had committed 8 different robberies in
various parts of Ningxia and killed a man during one attempt.
</P>
<P>
Five of the defendants, 1 of whom got the death sentence, have
appealed their sentences to the higher court on the grounds that
the punishment is excessive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
