<HEADLINE> Scaffolding Collapse Kills Two in Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 8 (Xinhua) -- At least two construction workers
were killed and nine others injured when the scaffolding around a
four-story building under construction collapsed in the West Bank
town of Ramallah Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Israeli security forces sent ambulances and fire-fighters to
the Palestinian self-rule area within several minutes after the
Palestinian National Authority asked them to help rescue victims,
Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said workers were building the roof when the
scaffolding collapsed. The specific cause of the incident is not
immediatley known.
</P>
<P>
Building has flourished since Israel handed over the city in
central West Bank to Palestinian rule in 1995 under the Oslo
peace accord. 
</P>
</TEXT>
