<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Anti-Drug Delegation Leaves for Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A Myanmar anti-drug delegation left
here Thursday for the Russian Federation to pay a goodwill visit
to the country.
</P>
<P>
It is led by Home Minister Colonel Tin Hlaing, who is also
chairman of the Central Committee for Drug Abuse Control (CCDAC).
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar delegation is invited by the Union Security Board
(USB) of the Russian Federation, state-run Radio Myanmar reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In January 1997, the Myanmar CCDAC and the USB of the Russian
Federation signed an agreement in Yangon on cooperation in the
fight against drug abuse and illicit drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
It is the first Myanmar official delegation to visit the
Russian Federation since October 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
