<HEADLINE> Salt Lake Set to Cut Expenses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Salt Lake City is set to cut 113
million U.S. dollars from its 2002 Winter Olympic Games
expenditure, reports said Thurdady.
</P>
<P>
A revised operating budget was being presented later on
Thursday to the management committee of organisers SLOC, which
would trim the gap between income and expenditure from 300 million
U.S. dollars to 187 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
"We have reduced our shortfall by making reductions in our
budget, adding new revenue from our corporate partners and working
with the U.S. Olympic Committee and the IOC," SLOC president Mitt
Romney was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
If passed, the revised budget will go to SLOC for final
approval on September 9.
</P>
<P>
A line-by-line review of the overal 1.45 billion U.S. dollars
budget has been carried out. Organisers have also been helped by
one new sponsor and three new suppliers. The revised overall
budget is now put at $1.34 billion, reports said. 
</P>
