<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Mixed in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed mixed in Tokyo
Thursday in a dull market, with the Nikkei index hovering around
the 18,000 crucial line.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange inched up 8.75 points, or 0.05
percent, from Wednesday's close to end at 17,967.65, marking the
first gain in three days.
</P>
<P>
However, the broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX),
covering all First Section issues, lost 7.93 points or 0.54
percent to 1,469.09.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section thinned to 597.15 million shares
from Wednesday's 644.97 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi Electric was Thursday's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Trading thinned out during the day, stuck between profit-taking
above the Nikkei's 18,000 line and buying on dips below its 17,900
level, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outnumbered
gainers 685 to 506, with 133 issues finishing unchanged.
</P>
<P>
On the Tokyo Foreign Exchange, the U.S. dollar firmed against
the yen in a market that had little sense of direction.
</P>
<P>
The dollar was quoted at 122.37-40 yen at 5 p.m., up from 122.
32-35 yen at 9 a.m., and from 122.20-30 yen in late overnight
trading in New York. It traded at 121.95-98 yen late Wednesday in
Tokyo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
