<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Share Prices closed higher on the
Singapore Stock Market Thursday supported by bargain hunters and
institutional buyers, and also the overnight rally on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) ended 15.33 points
higher to close at 2,159.86 points.
</P>
<P>
The volume totaled 836.57 million shares valued at 987.02
million Singapore dollars (580.59 million U.S. dollars). Gainers
led losers by 322 to 37 with 88 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Hotung led the active chart of the day with 50.90 million
shares changing hands. It was followed by AFP that had 40.42
million units done. IPC was the next with 28.13 counters traded.
</P>
<P>
GE Life and OUE led the gainers of the day rising 60 cents each
to close at 22.30 and 5.50 Singapore dollars respectively. Bukit
Sem ran up 40 cents to finish at 17.60 Singapore dollars. Auric
Pac, SIA DBScw00 and UOB gained 30 cents to end at 2.00, 8.30 and
11.40 Singapore dollars separately.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SPH headed the descent of the day shedding 80
cents to close at 30.00 Singapore dollars. SPH 100 lost 60 cents
to finish at 30.00 Singapore dollars. DBS F dropped 50 cents to
end at 19.80 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that most of the panic and forced selling that
dominated the week appeared to be over.
</P>
<P>
They noted that the market should start to recover but it would
not rise at the same pace as it did earlier this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
