<HEADLINE> Sino-American Project To Deal With Trash Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-American facility for
getting rid of trash will soon be built in the city of Xiangtan in
central China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, it will involve using trash to
produce useful organic fertilizer, diesel oil for automobiles, and
red bricks, glass, rubber, and marsh gas.
</P>
<P>
The project will be built on an 8-hectare area in two stages by
the Hunan New Energy Development Corporation and Import and Export
Equipment Investment Co. of the United States at a cost of 190
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
When the two phases are finished, it will be able to treat 300,
000 tons of trash annually.
</P>
<P>
Trash disposal in cities has become an important topic for
research in many countries and has been called a "sunrise industry
".
</P>
<P>
At present, the most popular methods of dealing with trash
range from burying it, putting it in compost heaps, or producing
heat and generating electricity by burning it. But China got a
later start than other countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
