<HEADLINE> Chinese Science Academy Launches High-tech Center In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences (
CAS) announced today here that its Shanghai branch will build a
high-tech research and development center.
</P>
<P>
CAS official Gui Wenzhuang says that it will have five
institutes for metallurgy, ceramics, organic chemistry, optics,
and physics that are expected to make contributions to the local
economy.
</P>
<P>
The center will also reform management through its employment
system and will look for research fellows from China and abroad.
All the institutes have plans to encourage the commercial use of
scientific developments.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Institute of Organic Chemistry has set up a high-
tech enterprise that plans to build four industrial centers within
two years. 
</P>
