<HEADLINE> PNG Urged to Correct Erroneous Decision on PNG-Taiwan "Diplomatic Ties" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokeswoman reiterated today that China hopes the Papua New
Guinean government would immediately correct its erroneous
decision of establishing "diplomatic ties" with Taiwan so as to
bring the relations between China and PNG back onto the normal
track.
</P>
<P>
Spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue made the remark at a regular press
conference when asked to comment on the resignation of PNG Prime
Minister Bill Skate.
</P>
<P>
Despite China's strong opposition, PNG Foreign Minister Roy
Yaki signed Monday with Taiwan's "Foreign Minister" Jason Hu a
communique on the formation of so-called "diplomatic ties" between
PNG and Taiwan during PNG Prime Minister Bill Skate's visit to
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
China has made solemn representations to and lodged a strong
protest against the Papua New Guinean government over its signing
of the so-called communique on the establishment of "diplomatic
ties" with Taiwan, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
The aforementioned actions by a handful people in the PNG
government have met strong opposition from the far-sighted
personnel within and outside the PNG government and the PNG people,
Zhang said, adding that the actions have also been widely
criticized by public opinion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
