<HEADLINE> 47 Major Government-Run Projects Completed in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Minister of Economic
Development and Cooperation Girma Birru has announced that 47
major government-run projects were completed during the just-ended
1998/99 fiscal year ending on July 7.
</P>
<P>
The state-run newspaper Ethiopian Herald Thursday quoted Girma
as saying that the 47 completed projects were among the 253 new
and outstanding projects which were under various stages of
construction throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
Among the 253 projects, 177 were carried over from the previous
years and 76 launched during the year, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, 50 percent of the projects cover
road- building, 13.7 percent transport and communications, 10
percent agriculture, seven percent education and six percent
energy while the rest are related to construction and other
economic sectors.
</P>
<P>
The projects, undertaken within the framework of the country's
five-year development program, focus on the improvement and
expansion of infrastructures, Girma said, adding most of the 2.9
billion birr (about 350 million U.S. dollars) allocated for the
year had been utilized for the various phases of activities.
</P>
<P>
Referring to road-building projects which constitute about half
of the project works with a total mileage of close to 2,000
kilometers, the minister said "this is the first time the country
is deploying so many contractors at a time for road building
projects." 
</P>
</TEXT>
