<DOCNO> XIE19990708.0312 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOSOC Adopts Ministerial Communique on Poverty Eradication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Economic and
Social Council (ECOSC) adopted a ministerial communique here
Wednesday stressing that productive employment played a central
role in poverty eradication.
</P>
<P>
The communique, adopted at the high-level segment of the 1999
session of the ECOSOC, said that strategies to eradicate poverty,
promote productive employment and achieve gender equality should
be designed to address the conditions and needs of women and men
on equal and equitable terms.
</P>
<P>
Ministers and heads of delegations also agreed that in many
cases, women and men suffered poverty or became impoverished for
different reasons and through different processes, and faced
different opportunities and constraints in coping with poverty and
in accessing labor markets and sustainable livelihoods.
</P>
<P>
Employment of people, in particular that of women, was a
prerequisite for effective poverty eradication and employment
creation strategies, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
The communique called on the international community to support
efforts to eradicate poverty, promote productive employment and
achieve gender equality and encourage members states to adopt and
implement legislation to ensure the elimination of violence
against women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
