<DOCNO> XIE19990708.0316 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> McDonald's Expanding Business in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The McDonald's Anhui Co., Ltd., a new
subsidiary of the McDonald's Company of the United States, was set
up recently in Hefei, capital of east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
The move represents a starting point of a massive program of
McDonald's to expand its business in the central and western parts
of China, said James Chu, vice-president of McDonald's China
Development Co.
</P>
<P>
According to Chu, the fast food giant has been operating 235
restaurants in 41 Chinese cities since it opened its first store
in Shenzhen, the country's first special economic zone in south
China's Guangdong Province. Of these restaurants, the majority are
located in relatively developed eastern and southern areas of the
country.
</P>
<P>
Chu said McDonald's has targeted Anhui because the province has
an increasingly improved business environment and a population of
62 million, a huge potential market.
</P>
<P>
The McDonald's Anhui Co., Ltd. has a total investment of five
million U.S. dollars and has a registered capital of three million
U.S. dollars. It is scheduled to open its first restaurant in
Hefei at the end of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
