<HEADLINE> New Funds On Shanghai, Shenzhen Stock Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Two new funds on the Shanghai and
Shenzhen stock exchanges -- Xinghe securities fund on the Shanghai
Exchange and Pufeng securities fund on the Shenzhen Exchange --
raised 6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Each of them issued 3 billion closed-end 15-year shares selling
for 1.01 yuan. The two investment funds bring to 38 the number of
funds on the two stock exchanges, and securities analysts say that
the two new investment funds show the maturity of China's
securities market.
</P>
<P>
The Huaxia Funds Management Co. will manage Xinghe and the
Penghua Fund Management Co. will manage Pufeng. Corporate sources
say that 50 percent of the funds will be invested in stocks
closely related to the Shanghai and Shenzhen exchanges, with some
30 percent earmarked for blue chip stocks and the remainder for
treasury bonds.
</P>
<P>
Investing in index-related stocks allows investors to share the
fruits of China's economic expansion and growing securities market.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
