<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Rejects U.S. Proposal for "World Tibet Day" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tibet is an inalienable part of Chinese territory and Tibetan
affairs are the internal affairs of China and no foreign country
has the right to interfere in them, said Foreign Ministry
spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue at a news conference here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
A small group of U.S. congresspeople have ignored these facts
and put forward the proposal to set up a "World Tibet Day" and
made irresponsible remarks on the Tibet issue in an attempt to use
that issue to interfere in China's internal affairs, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
China is resolutely opposed to this and extremely unhappy about
it, she said, and urged these congresspeople to immediately stop
interfering in China's internal affairs and to stop harming Sino-U.
S. relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
