<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures: China's Trade with France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Following is China's major exports
to the France and imports from it for the first five months this
year, according to the statistics released by the General
Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
China's export volume of machines and electronic products,
including audio and video equipments to France reached 307.615
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Its exports of textile raw material and products to France
valued at 146.176 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Its export volume of shoes, hats, umbrellas to France valued at
66.484 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
China's import volume of machines and electronic products,
including audio and video equipments from France reached 526.174
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Its import volume of automobiles, air vehicles, ships and other
transportation equipment from France reached 408.66 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Its import volume of chemical products and relevant industrial
products from France reached 109.049 million. 
</P>
