<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, July 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB -- A border agreement was drafted by Croatia and its
neighbor Bosnia-Herzegovina Wednesday in Zagreb, capital of
Croatia, a high-ranking Croatian official said.
</P>
<P>
Zeljko Dobranovich, head of the Croatian delegation for border
talks, was cited by the State TV and Broadcasting Service as
saying that the talks were successful and the settlement of the
1001-kilometer border issue would contribute to regional stability.
(Croatia-Bosnia-Border )
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- NATO General-Secretary Javier Solana announced
here Wednesday that a stability plan for the Balkans will be
unveiled at the end of this month, with its implementation
guaranteed jointly by the military bloc, the United Nations, the
World Bank and the Organization for Security and Co-operation in
Europe (OSCE).
</P>
<P>
Solana, who made the announcement in talks with Romanian Prime
Minister Radu Vasile, assured that the plan, which covers
political, economic and security sectors, will turn a new leaf in
the history of the crisis-ridden region. (Solana-Balkans-Stability
)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KATHMANDU -- All the five persons, one American national and
four Indian nationals, were killed when a cargo plane of the
German Lufthansa Airlines crashed Wednesday evening in the
Kathmandu Valley, the Tribhuvan International Airport (TIA) said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An airport source said their bodies were found scattered. Among
the dead, Captain Ricardo Nicolas Gonhalez was an American citizen.
(Nepal-Plane Crash-Death)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif arrived at
Lahore, capital of eastern province of Punjab, Thursday morning by
a civil flight, following his short visit to the United States and
the United Kingdom, informed officials here said.
</P>
<P>
